<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,394,851]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,466,491]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">Description.</emphasis>
Sponge grows upright reticular, composed of 
<quantity box="[896,1025,466,490]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2 to 5 mm</quantity>
thick fibres, rarely forming wider, flattened structures (
<figureCitation box="[381,448,502,526]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phorbas megasigma Ríos &amp; Cristobo, 2007, pictures of SMF 11817. A, habit in ethanol. B. skeletal section. C, acanthostyle I, D, acanthostyle II, E, tornote, F – G, three different specimens of arcuate isochelae, I, sigma. Scale bars: A: 10 mm, B: 1 mm, C: 100 µm, D – E, I: 30 µm, F – H: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249028/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[434,448,502,526]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Fibres regularly intercrossing, often in rectangular pattern. Surface bristled, knotty, porous, often with small openings (
<quantity box="[550,639,538,562]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
) piercing through entire sponge body. Consistency rather soft, spongy. Color in ethanol brownish beige.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,394,851]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Skeleton: Made up of plumose tracts of acanthostyles, interconnected by irregularly scattered acanthostyles (
<figureCitation box="[159,226,646,670]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phorbas megasigma Ríos &amp; Cristobo, 2007, pictures of SMF 11817. A, habit in ethanol. B. skeletal section. C, acanthostyle I, D, acanthostyle II, E, tornote, F – G, three different specimens of arcuate isochelae, I, sigma. Scale bars: A: 10 mm, B: 1 mm, C: 100 µm, D – E, I: 30 µm, F – H: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249028/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,226,646,670]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
B). In epidermis, echinating bundles of tornotes present. Chelae regularly distributed throughout the tissue.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,394,851]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Spiculation (
<tableCitation box="[341,415,682,706]" captionStart="TABLE 6" captionStartId="29.[151,239,894,918]" captionText="TABLE 6. Spicule sizes of Phorbas megasigma Ríos &amp; Cristobo, 2007. Values in µm are given as follows: minimum – mean – maximum (number of spicules measured). For comparison, values from Ríos &amp; Cristobo (2007), and Koltun (1964, P. nexus) are given." pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Tab. 
<number box="[398,415,682,706]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="6.0">6</number>
</tableCitation>
): Main spicules acanthostyles (
<figureCitation box="[765,831,682,706]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phorbas megasigma Ríos &amp; Cristobo, 2007, pictures of SMF 11817. A, habit in ethanol. B. skeletal section. C, acanthostyle I, D, acanthostyle II, E, tornote, F – G, three different specimens of arcuate isochelae, I, sigma. Scale bars: A: 10 mm, B: 1 mm, C: 100 µm, D – E, I: 30 µm, F – H: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249028/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[817,831,682,706]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
C), 
<number box="[880,978,682,706]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="582.5" valueMax="645.0" valueMin="520.0">520–645</number>
µm in length and 
<number box="[1182,1251,682,706]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="20.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="15.0">15–25</number>
µm in diameter. Additionally, smaller acanthostyles occur (
<figureCitation box="[649,720,718,742]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phorbas megasigma Ríos &amp; Cristobo, 2007, pictures of SMF 11817. A, habit in ethanol. B. skeletal section. C, acanthostyle I, D, acanthostyle II, E, tornote, F – G, three different specimens of arcuate isochelae, I, sigma. Scale bars: A: 10 mm, B: 1 mm, C: 100 µm, D – E, I: 30 µm, F – H: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249028/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[706,720,718,742]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
D), 
<number box="[781,878,718,742]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="292.5" valueMax="410.0" valueMin="175.0">175–410</number>
µm in length with diameter 
<number box="[1228,1285,718,742]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="12.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="5.0">5–20</number>
µm. Further megascleres tornotes (
<figureCitation box="[400,465,754,778]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phorbas megasigma Ríos &amp; Cristobo, 2007, pictures of SMF 11817. A, habit in ethanol. B. skeletal section. C, acanthostyle I, D, acanthostyle II, E, tornote, F – G, three different specimens of arcuate isochelae, I, sigma. Scale bars: A: 10 mm, B: 1 mm, C: 100 µm, D – E, I: 30 µm, F – H: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249028/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[451,465,754,778]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
E), 
<number box="[512,609,754,778]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="362.5" valueMax="420.0" valueMin="305.0">305–420</number>
µm in length and 
<number box="[813,827,754,778]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="5.0">5</number>
µm in diameter. Main microscleres unguiferate chelae (
<figureCitation box="[159,228,790,814]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phorbas megasigma Ríos &amp; Cristobo, 2007, pictures of SMF 11817. A, habit in ethanol. B. skeletal section. C, acanthostyle I, D, acanthostyle II, E, tornote, F – G, three different specimens of arcuate isochelae, I, sigma. Scale bars: A: 10 mm, B: 1 mm, C: 100 µm, D – E, I: 30 µm, F – H: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249028/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,228,790,814]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
F-H), 
<number box="[309,378,790,814]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="17.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="15.0">15–20</number>
µm in length. The characteristic large sigmas (
<figureCitation box="[925,994,790,814]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[187,1399,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phorbas megasigma Ríos &amp; Cristobo, 2007, pictures of SMF 11817. A, habit in ethanol. B. skeletal section. C, acanthostyle I, D, acanthostyle II, E, tornote, F – G, three different specimens of arcuate isochelae, I, sigma. Scale bars: A: 10 mm, B: 1 mm, C: 100 µm, D – E, I: 30 µm, F – H: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249028/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[980,994,790,814]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
G) extremely rare, but clearly present within the tissue,about 
<number box="[411,509,826,850]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="185.0" valueMax="270.0" valueMin="100.0">100–270</number>
µm x 
<number box="[581,687,826,850]" pageId="29" pageNumber="57" value="75.75" valueMax="105.0" valueMin="46.5">46.5–105</number>
µm.
</paragraph>
